            <div>
               
	<pb facs="liv_002135_0001" n="0001"/><!-- Change both @facs and @n -->
	<!-- Start each page with a <pb> formatted as above -->
<lb/><fw n="152"><space extent="4" unit="words"/><add place="margintop" rend="gray small" hand="#U">152</add></fw>
<lb/>
<lb/><opener><dateline rend="center"><!-- Maybe I am missing something, but I dono't see Hadley Green anywhere?  I see Newstead Abbey, etc? SF --><!-- Yes, mistake. AW --><date when="1864-12-06">6 <choice><abbr>Dec</abbr><expan>December</expan></choice><!-- Change line info as appropriate --><!-- Begin each line with <lb/> as here --> 1864</date></dateline><!-- Change line info as appropriate -->
<lb/>    
<lb/><salute>My Dear Moore</salute></opener><!-- Change line info as appropriate -->
<lb/><p>My daughter
<lb/><persName>Agnes</persName> will attend
<lb/>to the photos - Hence
<lb/>not seen <persName>Farebrother</persName>
<lb/>but <term type="occupation"><persName>D<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> Tidman</persName></term> sent
<lb/>a note desiring to
<lb/>know where I was
<lb/>that he might call
<lb/>on me - I therefore
<lb/>went but missed him 

	<pb facs="liv_002135_0002" n="0002"/>
<lb/><unclear cert="medium">I only</unclear> wanted to
<lb/>know if you
<lb/>had got the things
<lb/>as I feared they 
<lb/>had been lost -
<lb/>You will excuse
<lb/><persName>Agnes</persName> finishing
<lb/>this as I am very
<lb/>busy -<persName><choice><abbr>DL</abbr><expan>David Livingstone</expan></choice></persName>. <!--Is this a closer? EC-->

<addSpan spanTo="#add1" hand="#AL"/><!-- Is this right, or do we use <div resp="#AL"? SF -->
<lb/>I have great pleasure
<lb/>in enclosing <persName>Papa</persName>'s
<lb/><foreign xml:lang="fr">"cartes."</foreign> They are not
<lb/>so good as I should
<lb/>like them to be, but

	<pb facs="liv_002135_0003" n="0003"/>
<lb/><fw n="153"><space extent="4" unit="words"/><add place="margintop" rend="gray small" hand="#U">153</add></fw>
<lb/>I suppose all <foreign xml:lang="fr">carte
<lb/>de visites</foreign> are the same,
<lb/>I say don't think the
<lb/>large "head" is <hi rend="underline">good</hi>
<lb/><gap extent="3" unit="words"/> I am such
<lb/><gap extent="3" unit="words"/> my life
<lb/><gap extent="3" unit="words"/> as if <!--Large hole in paper spanning three lines. EC-->
<lb/>they should jump
<lb/>out of their sockets!
<lb/>You will see by his
<lb/>short note that he
<lb/>is very busy &amp; cannot
<lb/>write more</p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">Please don't show

	<pb facs="liv_002135_0004" n="0004"/>
<lb/>the ugly one off - It
<lb/>will give <unclear cert="low">hangers</unclear><!-- Can't make this out either! SF -->
<lb/>such an idea of
<lb/>my Papa -</p><!-- Do we code this as a name as above? SF -->
<lb/><p rend="right">Believe me
<lb/><gap extent="3" unit="lines"/></p>
<lb/><p><date when="1864-12-07">7<hi rend="sup">th</hi> <hi rend="underline"><choice><abbr>Dec<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi></abbr><expan>December</expan></choice> 1864</hi></date></p>

<anchor xml:id="add1"/><!--Not sure if this is coded correctly, seems like it might be a postscript. EC-->

